# Known divergence: extended-query message sequencing on a plan-time error.
#
# For `SELECT 1/0` (Parse/Bind/Execute/Sync), PostgreSQL constant-folds 1/0 at
# plan time during Bind, so it sends ParseComplete then ErrorResponse and never
# BindComplete. The multigateway plans/executes lazily at Execute, so it emits
# BindComplete before the error. Matching PostgreSQL would require eager
# bind-time planning against the backend (an extra round-trip on the
# latency-sensitive query path) for negligible client benefit, so we record the
# divergence here instead of fixing it.
#
# Effect: add the extra `<= BE BindComplete` line to PostgreSQL's trace so it
# matches what the multigateway produces.
--- a
+++ b
@@ -20,6 +20,7 @@
 FE=> Execute(portal="p_dz")
 FE=> Sync
 <= BE ParseComplete
+<= BE BindComplete
 <= BE ErrorResponse(C 22012)
 <= BE ReadyForQuery(I)
 FE=> Query (query="SELECT count(*) FROM pgproto_err")
